---
// One idea: the meaning is in the pauses — the small silences put back between
// the bones, the interval that lets a sentence phrase.
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 560 180" role="img" aria-labelledby="sil-t">
  <title id="sil-t">On the left, a run of vertebrae crammed together with no gaps — a run-on, unreadable. On the right, the same vertebrae with small marked silences restored between them, so the line can phrase and breathe.</title>
  <!-- crammed, no silences -->
  <g class="ink block"><path d="M60 50 L 108 46 M60 66 L 108 62 M60 82 L 108 78 M60 98 L 108 94 M60 114 L 108 110" /></g>
  <text class="hand-label" x="52" y="140" font-size="13" opacity="0.7">no pauses — a run-on</text>
  <!-- restored silences -->
  <g class="ink block"><path d="M420 44 L 468 40 M420 70 L 468 66 M420 96 L 468 92 M420 122 L 468 118" /></g>
  <g class="ink hair" stroke="var(--poppy)"><path d="M440 52 l 8 0 M440 78 l 8 0 M440 104 l 8 0" /></g>
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="330" y="90" font-size="14">the silence carries it</text>
  <path class="ink hair" d="M150 80 C 220 78, 300 82, 372 80" stroke-dasharray="2 6" opacity="0.6" />
</svg>
